  stimulus_text = 'The author writes, “We need to be mindful of the ways in which our own experiences can shape our perceptions and beliefs.  We are all susceptible to biases and assumptions, but by acknowledging these tendencies, we can strive to create more inclusive and equitable understanding.” What is the author’s main point in this passage? Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
